                    <p>STEP and IEEE recently hosted a wind turbine competition for 1st year engineering students. Contestants were provided with materials to build a scale model wind turbine which would be tested in a wind tunnel in the Fluids Lab. Competitors were responsible for designing the turbine blades and supporting structure using the least amount of material needed while stile achieving the required strength. For pictures of the event please check out our gallery.</p>
